  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I report fake app on Appstore?",
  "response": "If you come across a fake app on the App Store, it's important to report it to Apple so they can investigate and take appropriate action. Here\u2019s how you can report a fake app:\n\n### Steps to Report a Fake App on the App Store:\n1. **Open the App Store**:\n   - Launch the App Store on your iPhone, iPad, or Mac.\n\n2. **Find the App**:\n   - Search for the app you believe is fake or fraudulent.\n\n3. **Go to the App\u2019s Page**:\n   - Tap or click on the app to open its App Store page.\n\n4. **Scroll Down to the Developer Information**:\n   - On the app\u2019s page, scroll down to the \"Developer\" section to see the developer\u2019s name.\n\n5. **Report a Problem**:\n   - Scroll further down to the \"Ratings & Reviews\" section.\n   - Tap or click on the developer\u2019s name under the \"Developer\" section. This will take you to the developer\u2019s page.\n   - On the developer\u2019s page, scroll to the bottom and select **\"Report a Problem\"**. This will open the Apple Support website in your browser.\n\n6. **Sign in and Submit Your Report**:\n   - Log in with your Apple ID if prompted.\n   - Select the issue type that best describes the problem (e.g., \"Report a scam or fraud\" or \"Report offensive content\").\n   - Provide details about why you believe the app is fake or fraudulent (e.g., misleading information, stolen content, etc.). Be as specific as possible.\n   - Submit the report.\n\n### Alternative Methods:\n- **Contact Apple Support**:\n  - Visit [Apple Support](https://support.apple.com/) and contact them directly to report the issue.\n- **Email Apple**:\n  - You can email Apple at `reportphishing@apple.com` if you suspect phishing or fraudulent activity.\n\n### What to Include in Your Report:\n- The app\u2019s name and link to its App Store page.\n- Details about why you believe the app is fake or fraudulent.\n- Any evidence (e.g., screenshots).\n\nBy reporting fake apps, you help keep the App Store safe and reliable for all users. Apple takes these reports seriously and will investigate accordingly.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
